PRISTINA, Kosovo â The Kosovo police reached an agreement on Thursday (April 2nd) to allow the EULEX police to use its information technology and communication system. EULEX police chief Rainer Kuehn said the support by the Kosovo police will facilitate communication between EULEX officials and will help in their daily work. EULEX users inside Kosovo police stations will now have access to servers and telephone systems through the police's communication network. (Koha Ditore, Lajm, Express, Kosova Sot - 03/04/09) 
